Author: ponkypink#7913
Content: So for this particular case, we have a 52 character private key in WIF format with the first part missing. But we know that for this coin a private key always starts with a U and the second character can only be from p to x. If you then look closely at the picture you can see the bottom part of the 3rd and it can only be a d or u, the 4th is also partially visible and is either an N or W
